g.text: Set by CPU on read access
Set by CPU on write access

div.p: Note: PDE/PTE is simpler than GDT - only 4 bytes:

ul.li: Bytes 0-1: Low 16 bits of frame address + flags in low 12 bits
Bytes 2-3: High 16 bits of frame address
Frame address must be 4KB aligned (bits 0-11 always 0 in address)
Combined with flags in bits 0-11 for storage efficiency

g.title: Accessed: set by CPU on read
Dirty: set by CPU on write
Global: not flushed on CR3 reload
Accessed: set by CPU on read
Dirty: set by CPU on write
Global: not flushed on CR3 reload
